thy glory in the Summer-months , With light , and heat , severe
the lucid shower Of beamy fruits
Yet so harmonious mixed , so fitly joined , One
one in such enchanting sort , Shade , unperceived
Thee not , marks not the mighty hand , That , ever-busy , wheels the silent spheres

shoots , steaming , thence The fair profusion that overspreads the Spring
touches all the springs of life
the brown void with a religious awe
the humid maze Along the vale
lays the warbling world asleep , Sweetest of birds ! sweet Philomela
the shepherd's flute , the virgin's chant , The prompting seraph , and the poet's lyre , Still sing the God of Seasons
